    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Struct to hold batch <ref refid="classopentelemetry_1_1sdk_1_1logs_1_1LogRecordProcessor" kindref="compound">LogRecordProcessor</ref> options.</para>
<para>This is an aggregate type that supports C++20 designated initializers. Default values are read from environment variables when an instance is created:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>OTEL_BLRP_MAX_QUEUE_SIZE (default: 2048)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OTEL_BLRP_SCHEDULE_DELAY (default: 1000ms)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OTEL_BLRP_EXPORT_TIMEOUT (default: 30000ms)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OTEL_BLRP_MAX_EXPORT_BATCH_SIZE (default: 512)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Usage notes:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>If you use default initialization (e.g., <computeroutput><ref refid="structopentelemetry_1_1sdk_1_1logs_1_1BatchLogRecordProcessorOptions" kindref="compound">BatchLogRecordProcessorOptions</ref> opts{}</computeroutput>), all fields are set by reading the environment variables (or hardcoded defaults if unset).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If you use aggregate initialization with explicit values (positional or designated), those values override the environment variable defaults for the specified fields.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>With C++20 designated initializers, you can override only specific fields; unspecified fields will use environment variables or hardcoded defaults. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
